WEBVTT

00:45.312 --> 00:46.511
<i> [tense music]</i>

00:46.513 --> 00:47.780
- [groans softly]

00:47.915 --> 00:49.514
[groan echoing]

00:49.650 --> 00:51.650
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

00:51.652 --> 00:53.686
[sighs]

00:58.325 --> 01:00.893
[groans]

01:03.798 --> 01:05.330
[horn blares in distance]

01:05.466 --> 01:06.399
[high-pitched ringing]

01:06.533 --> 01:08.467
[groans]

01:09.737 --> 01:10.936
[thuds]
Nope.

01:11.072 --> 01:11.971
Oh...

01:14.209 --> 01:15.875
[sighs]

01:16.010 --> 01:19.145
[train tracks rattling]

01:22.217 --> 01:23.950
Shh...

01:27.622 --> 01:30.689
<i> [tense music]</i>

01:30.691 --> 01:37.864
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:43.771 --> 01:45.037
Hello?

01:45.172 --> 01:47.039
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:47.174 --> 01:49.442
Ben? Alex?

01:49.577 --> 01:56.749
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:03.458 --> 02:04.723
[door beeps]

02:04.725 --> 02:09.462
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:09.596 --> 02:12.465
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

02:12.599 --> 02:13.933
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:14.068 --> 02:15.468
Whoa, whoa!
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

02:15.603 --> 02:18.271
Hey. Okay.

02:18.405 --> 02:19.472
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:19.606 --> 02:21.140
Stop. Stop!

02:21.276 --> 02:23.408
All right, hey.
Hey, take it easy.

02:23.544 --> 02:25.077
All right.

02:25.212 --> 02:26.913
[groans]

02:28.082 --> 02:29.882
Who are you?
- Don't play dumb.

02:30.017 --> 02:31.416
What were you doing
in the Engine?

02:31.552 --> 02:33.486
- You're in a lot of trouble.

02:33.621 --> 02:35.154
- Hey. Hey, hey, hey.

02:35.156 --> 02:37.490
No, no, no.
Hey. Hey. Hey, hey.

02:37.624 --> 02:39.091
Listen, I don't know
what you--

02:39.226 --> 02:40.826
[door opens]

02:40.828 --> 02:41.827
- Hello, chaps.

02:41.829 --> 02:43.562
- Shit.

02:43.564 --> 02:46.365
[gunshots]
- Oh! Oh!

02:46.501 --> 02:48.033
Hey! Jesus!

02:48.169 --> 02:50.503
- That was too close, Andre.

02:50.637 --> 02:52.437
Clean him up.

02:52.439 --> 02:54.573
- Javi?
- Yeah.

02:54.709 --> 02:56.175
- Have you got it?
- Got what?

02:56.311 --> 02:57.376
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:57.512 --> 02:58.777
Ruth?

02:58.913 --> 03:00.379
- Oh, shut up.
You're ruining this.

03:00.515 --> 03:02.114
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:02.249 --> 03:03.716
- Yeah. He's got it.
- Good.

03:03.851 --> 03:05.384
- Come on. Let's clear out.
This'll draw heat.

03:05.386 --> 03:07.653
- Calmly now. Calmly.

03:07.788 --> 03:08.988
We split up
and meet at the border.

03:09.123 --> 03:10.389
Everybody got their papers?

03:10.391 --> 03:12.325
- Yeah.
- Good. Come on. Let's go.

03:12.459 --> 03:14.660
- Okay. Let's go.

03:14.795 --> 03:18.331
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:18.465 --> 03:19.598
- What?

03:19.734 --> 03:23.269
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:24.471 --> 03:27.340
<i> [light music]</i>

03:27.474 --> 03:28.807
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:28.809 --> 03:30.943
What the...

03:31.078 --> 03:34.146
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

03:34.281 --> 03:39.552
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:39.687 --> 03:41.554
Winnie?

03:41.689 --> 03:43.088
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:43.224 --> 03:44.423
Why not?

03:44.559 --> 03:51.697
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:03.778 --> 04:05.644
[chuckles]

04:05.780 --> 04:08.181
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:08.315 --> 04:10.583
[laughing] Yeah.

04:10.718 --> 04:11.650
Uh...

04:11.786 --> 04:13.318
Till. Wow. Okay.

04:13.320 --> 04:15.054
Hey, you gotta help me.
I need--

04:15.056 --> 04:17.456
- Shh. Inside voices.

04:17.592 --> 04:19.124
- Yeah, that's about enough
of this nightmare.

04:19.126 --> 04:20.325
[whispers]
I have to wake up.

04:20.327 --> 04:21.394
- Hey, buddy,

04:21.528 --> 04:23.862
you gotta get
your shit together, okay?

04:23.998 --> 04:25.598
You're not dreaming.

04:25.733 --> 04:26.866
[whispers]
You're dying.

04:27.001 --> 04:29.869
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

04:30.004 --> 04:37.143
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:40.081 --> 04:42.948
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

04:43.084 --> 04:50.189
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

05:03.037 --> 05:06.439
[indistinct chatter]

05:06.573 --> 05:07.640
- Hey.
- Hey.

05:07.775 --> 05:09.908
- It's first light.
The vigil's over.

05:09.910 --> 05:11.711
- Let's go get our boy.

05:14.649 --> 05:15.781
- Layton.

05:15.916 --> 05:17.382
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

05:17.384 --> 05:19.051
Layton.

05:19.186 --> 05:20.319
- Layton.

05:20.455 --> 05:22.121
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

05:22.256 --> 05:23.656
- His pulse is weak.
Go and get Dr. Pelton.

05:23.791 --> 05:24.790
Quick, quick, go.

05:24.925 --> 05:27.592
- Okay. Okay.
- [snapping]

05:27.594 --> 05:30.262
Layton, wake up.

05:30.397 --> 05:32.131
<i> [whispering] Wake up.</i>
- [snapping]

05:32.133 --> 05:35.734
Wake up. Wake up.
- Hey.

05:35.870 --> 05:37.069
- Wake up.
- Hey.

05:37.204 --> 05:38.604
Cool it,
or you'll get us both

05:38.739 --> 05:40.405
thrown in the slammer.

05:40.541 --> 05:43.142
You can't mess around here,
okay?

05:43.278 --> 05:45.077
- Where is here?
- This is Snowpiercer.

05:45.212 --> 05:46.745
- This is not Snowpiercer.
- No, it is.

05:46.881 --> 05:48.147
And it isn't.

05:48.283 --> 05:49.748
You'll recognize people,
but they're not the same

05:49.884 --> 05:51.016
as they are over there.

05:51.018 --> 05:53.018
- You're the same. Sort of.

05:53.020 --> 05:54.287
- I'm the librarian.

05:54.421 --> 05:55.621
I know things.

05:55.756 --> 05:57.823
You're still carrying residue
from the other side.

05:57.958 --> 05:59.758
[blows] But it will fade.

05:59.760 --> 06:01.827
You'll get used to it here.
- No. "Used to it"?

06:01.962 --> 06:04.163
No. Till, I need to get home.

06:04.299 --> 06:07.566
- Oh. Well, that's different.

06:07.568 --> 06:08.701
I don't think
I can help you with that.

06:08.836 --> 06:10.235
- Why not?

06:10.371 --> 06:11.971
- Well, first, you'd have
to see the Tail Boss.

06:12.106 --> 06:13.906
But that's a dangerous journey,

06:14.041 --> 06:15.908
you know want I'm saying?

06:16.043 --> 06:18.110
- Nope, I don't.
- Okay. Work with me.

06:18.245 --> 06:23.582
If you want to get back,
you need to find the Tail

06:23.584 --> 06:27.186
and ask the Tail Boss
to send you home.

06:27.322 --> 06:30.589
- Wilford, he was pretending
to be my buddy

06:30.725 --> 06:33.792
and he was gonna cross
the border for some mission,

06:33.928 --> 06:35.861
but I needed papers.

06:35.997 --> 06:38.797
- Oh.
Now, that I can help you with.

06:38.799 --> 06:39.999
- Okay.
- Follow me.

06:40.001 --> 06:41.867
- Yes.

06:42.003 --> 06:44.870
<i> [tense music]</i>

06:45.006 --> 06:50.876
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

06:51.012 --> 06:54.347
[machines beeping, whirring]

06:54.481 --> 06:55.614
- Got it.

06:55.616 --> 06:56.615
- Okay, on three.

06:56.751 --> 06:59.018
One, two, three.

06:59.020 --> 07:00.286
- How is he?

07:01.088 --> 07:02.355
Well, what does the doctor say?

07:02.489 --> 07:03.756
- Nothing yet.
She's with him now.

07:03.891 --> 07:05.691
We only just got here.

07:05.693 --> 07:08.627
- You said everything
was gonna be fine.

07:08.629 --> 07:10.696
- Josie. What happened?

07:10.831 --> 07:12.965
- I don't know.

07:13.100 --> 07:15.168
He just--he just
wouldn't wake up.

07:20.641 --> 07:26.311
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

07:26.447 --> 07:28.313
- The forger's
the next door down.

07:28.449 --> 07:29.848
Don't let on
you're not from here.

07:29.984 --> 07:31.250
- You're not coming?

07:31.252 --> 07:33.518
- I can't get you
to the Tail, Layton.

07:33.654 --> 07:34.920
Listen to me.

07:34.922 --> 07:37.189
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

07:37.324 --> 07:38.523
The longer you're here,

07:38.659 --> 07:40.859
the harder it is
to get to the other side.

07:40.995 --> 07:42.928
Do not get lost.

07:43.064 --> 07:44.129
[knife clicks, slashes]

07:44.131 --> 07:46.065
- What did you do that for?

07:46.200 --> 07:47.600
- Shh-shh-shh-shh-shh.
- [groans]

07:47.735 --> 07:49.668
- You don't have much time
in the real world.

07:49.670 --> 07:53.472
This cut will guide you
if you start to lose your way.

07:53.608 --> 07:54.807
Hmm?

07:54.942 --> 07:57.410
- Thanks, I guess.
- Okay.

07:57.544 --> 07:59.478
Good luck, bud.

07:59.480 --> 08:00.545
You'll need it.

08:00.547 --> 08:05.818
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:05.953 --> 08:08.153
- [sucks in air]

08:08.155 --> 08:10.890
[scoffing]

08:11.025 --> 08:14.960
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:14.962 --> 08:16.561
[knocking]

08:16.563 --> 08:17.562
[door clicks open]

08:17.698 --> 08:18.964
[music playing faintly
in distance]

08:18.966 --> 08:20.566
both: Oh, shit.

08:20.701 --> 08:22.034
It's you.

08:22.169 --> 08:23.302
- Uh, I'm here for my papers.

08:23.304 --> 08:25.570
- Not in the hall.
Not in the hall.

08:25.572 --> 08:27.172
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:27.308 --> 08:32.645
<i> - ♪ I'm sure</i>
<i> it will come true ♪</i>

08:32.780 --> 08:34.447
- You want one?

08:34.581 --> 08:36.115
- No, thanks.

08:36.117 --> 08:37.783
- Good.

08:37.918 --> 08:40.786
<i> [singer singing indistinctly]</i>

08:40.921 --> 08:42.387
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:42.523 --> 08:44.657
Starts to wear on you,
doesn't it?

08:44.792 --> 08:45.658
[typewriter dings]

08:45.793 --> 08:46.859
[keys clacking]

08:46.994 --> 08:48.327
You tell yourself
your cover story

08:48.463 --> 08:51.264
so many times,
you start to forget

08:51.398 --> 08:53.598
what's real
and what you made up.

08:53.600 --> 08:54.934
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:55.069 --> 08:56.669
- I don't know about that.

08:56.804 --> 09:00.339
- You never started to believe
your own lie?

09:00.475 --> 09:03.876
Whatever, you don't have
to prove yourself to me.

09:04.011 --> 09:06.812
I am out of the game.

09:06.814 --> 09:08.013
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:08.149 --> 09:09.815
This is just
a little side hustle

09:09.950 --> 09:12.685
to keep me going.

09:12.820 --> 09:13.819
Sign here.

09:13.954 --> 09:15.288
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:15.422 --> 09:16.689
- This will get me in the Tail?

09:16.824 --> 09:19.358
- The Tail?
What, you got a death wish?

09:19.494 --> 09:21.760
- Uh, just the opposite,
actually.

09:21.762 --> 09:24.096
- Well, I don't mess
with the Tail.

09:24.231 --> 09:26.631
You understand?

09:26.633 --> 09:29.902
You want the Tail,
go see the Cartographer.

09:30.037 --> 09:31.304
- Cartographer?

09:31.438 --> 09:33.572
- Yes. In the Market.

09:33.708 --> 09:35.774
I'm gonna need
something in return.

09:35.776 --> 09:37.042
<i> [tense music]</i>

09:37.178 --> 09:40.045
Two operatives
got whacked uptrain.

09:40.181 --> 09:41.914
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:42.049 --> 09:44.183
I heard that you were involved,

09:44.319 --> 09:46.585
but I figure someone else
pulled the trigger.

09:46.721 --> 09:48.453
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:48.589 --> 09:50.923
So...

09:51.058 --> 09:53.658
you give me
the triggerman's name,

09:53.660 --> 09:56.595
and I will send you
on your way.

09:56.731 --> 09:59.999
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:00.001 --> 10:02.134
- I don't know,
and I don't rat.

10:02.269 --> 10:03.669
Keep your damn papers.

10:03.804 --> 10:09.208
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:09.210 --> 10:11.010
What's going on here, Ruth?

10:11.012 --> 10:12.144
- Just a little test.

10:12.279 --> 10:13.546
You screwed up and got caught.

10:13.681 --> 10:14.947
We need to know
we can trust you.

10:15.082 --> 10:16.815
- You have your answer.

10:16.817 --> 10:20.485
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:20.487 --> 10:22.088
- I got my eye on you.

10:26.961 --> 10:28.394
[machine beeping]

10:29.630 --> 10:31.697
- Any news?
- No.

10:31.832 --> 10:33.266
[baby fussing]

10:38.172 --> 10:40.740
- He's stable.
You can see him now.

10:42.109 --> 10:44.910
[machine whirring]

10:44.912 --> 10:46.579
[beeping]

10:46.714 --> 10:48.513
- Well, there's no
sugarcoating this.

10:48.649 --> 10:52.385
He's in a coma, has been
for up to 12 hours already.

10:52.519 --> 10:55.721
- Will he wake up?
- I wish I could tell you.

10:55.723 --> 10:57.522
CT scan shows
some brain swelling,

10:57.658 --> 11:00.525
but his pupils are responding,
so that's a good sign.

11:00.527 --> 11:01.794
- So what do we do now?

11:01.929 --> 11:07.400
- Stay strong, hold his hand,
talk to him.

11:07.534 --> 11:09.334
It's a waiting game,
I'm afraid,

11:09.470 --> 11:12.805
but you're welcome to stay.

11:14.942 --> 11:16.542
- I gotta go.

11:20.081 --> 11:21.880
- You keep us updated.

11:21.882 --> 11:22.849
- Yeah.

11:28.222 --> 11:30.355
- I have to get back
to the Engine.

11:30.357 --> 11:32.357
- Yeah.

11:32.493 --> 11:34.960
Yeah. I'll come too.
- You don't have to.

11:35.096 --> 11:36.762
He'd want you here.

11:38.766 --> 11:41.767
- Are you sure?
- Yeah.

11:50.177 --> 11:53.178
<i> [tense music]</i>

11:53.180 --> 11:55.114
- He passed.
- So far.

11:55.116 --> 11:57.450
- Course I passed.

11:57.585 --> 12:00.585
- I told her you were solid,
sport.

12:00.587 --> 12:02.254
Don't let me down.
- Yeah. I'm good.

12:02.389 --> 12:03.456
Let's go.
- Right.

12:03.591 --> 12:05.390
We cross the border
individually.

12:05.526 --> 12:08.994
Answer questions yes or no.

12:09.130 --> 12:10.729
Stick to your cover stories.

12:10.865 --> 12:11.931
We should be good.

12:12.066 --> 12:13.732
All right? Let's go.

12:13.734 --> 12:14.867
- All right.

12:15.002 --> 12:17.602
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:17.604 --> 12:20.339
- Hey.
Uh, what's my cover story?

12:20.341 --> 12:23.342
- You joking?
- No, I'm fine. I just forgot.

12:23.478 --> 12:25.811
- Well, tighten up.
You're a dancer.

12:25.813 --> 12:27.680
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:27.815 --> 12:28.681
- Name?

12:28.816 --> 12:30.149
- Joseph Wilford.

12:30.151 --> 12:31.416
- Purpose of travel?

12:31.552 --> 12:34.954
- Import-export.
Exotic fruit and sugars.

12:35.089 --> 12:36.889
Thank you.

12:37.024 --> 12:42.161
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:42.163 --> 12:43.896
- Name?

12:44.031 --> 12:45.965
- Andre Layton.

12:46.100 --> 12:47.900
- Name?

12:48.035 --> 12:49.302
- I just--Andre Layton.

12:49.436 --> 12:51.837
- Why were you uptrain?

12:51.839 --> 12:53.839
- I'm a dancer.

12:53.975 --> 12:55.240
- I love the ballet.

12:55.242 --> 12:57.042
- No, it's modern, actually.

12:57.044 --> 12:58.911
We had a recital.

13:01.516 --> 13:07.853
Dance is the hidden language
of the body...

13:07.855 --> 13:10.122
and soul.

13:10.257 --> 13:15.060
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:15.062 --> 13:16.395
- Sad I missed it.

13:16.397 --> 13:18.197
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:18.333 --> 13:19.464
- Next time.

13:19.600 --> 13:26.706
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:27.408 --> 13:28.608
[sighs]

13:34.082 --> 13:37.149
<i> [tense music]</i>

13:37.151 --> 13:44.123
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:45.560 --> 13:48.627
- [sobbing quietly]

13:48.629 --> 13:53.632
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:53.634 --> 13:55.367
- Hello?
- [gasps]

13:55.503 --> 13:57.103
Oh.

13:57.237 --> 13:59.438
You shouldn't be in here.

13:59.573 --> 14:02.708
- Well, I'm just hiding out.

14:02.843 --> 14:05.377
But I--I can leave.

14:05.379 --> 14:06.879
It's all yours.

14:10.118 --> 14:13.519
I heard about Layton.
I'm very sorry.

14:13.654 --> 14:15.521
- Yeah, I'm sure you are.

14:15.656 --> 14:18.724
[sniffling]

14:19.928 --> 14:22.128
- I've never
seen you cry before.

14:24.264 --> 14:27.533
You know,
you don't have to fight it.

14:27.668 --> 14:30.603
He was your best friend.

14:30.738 --> 14:32.705
- And there's nothing I can do
to help him.

14:34.408 --> 14:36.876
So--bye, Audrey.

14:46.621 --> 14:49.287
- You could talk to him.

14:49.289 --> 14:51.490
If he's still in there,
he'll hear you.

14:51.625 --> 14:53.826
<i> [soft music]</i>

14:53.828 --> 14:55.828
- And say what?

14:55.830 --> 14:58.096
- Remind him
what he's fighting for.

14:58.232 --> 15:00.699
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:00.835 --> 15:03.369
- You should do it.
- Me?

15:03.504 --> 15:05.504
- Like you used to
in the Nightcar.

15:05.506 --> 15:07.706
You get inside people's heads.

15:07.842 --> 15:09.175
That's your thing.

15:09.309 --> 15:10.509
- This is different.

15:10.511 --> 15:13.379
- You just told me
it's worth a try.

15:13.514 --> 15:16.649
Please, Audrey.

15:16.651 --> 15:19.585
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:19.720 --> 15:22.454
<i> [light music playing]</i>

15:22.590 --> 15:24.723
[indistinct chatter]

15:24.859 --> 15:29.728
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:29.864 --> 15:32.731
- Joe. Ruthie.

15:32.733 --> 15:34.200
Oh, you have just made my day.

15:34.334 --> 15:35.734
Get down here right now.

15:35.736 --> 15:36.869
- We're just dropping in.

15:37.005 --> 15:39.471
Brief respite. Come on, chaps.

15:39.607 --> 15:41.807
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:41.942 --> 15:44.410
- Oh...
- [chuckles]

15:44.545 --> 15:47.213
You, my dear, are radiant.

15:47.348 --> 15:50.416
- It is the humidity.
It makes me glow.

15:50.551 --> 15:51.684
- [chuckling] Oh.

15:51.819 --> 15:53.752
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:53.888 --> 15:55.221
- Now, how long
do I get to keep you?

15:55.356 --> 15:56.955
Come, I've got
your favorite table waiting.

15:56.957 --> 15:58.691
- Till the sun's over the yard,
at least.

15:58.826 --> 16:01.560
- Hey, hey. [speaks Spanish]
Come here.

16:01.562 --> 16:02.895
Two shots, please.

16:03.031 --> 16:04.630
- You forgot your manners.

16:04.765 --> 16:07.366
<i> - Perdón, señorita.</i>
Three shots.

16:07.368 --> 16:09.101
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

16:09.237 --> 16:10.502
[chuckles]

16:10.504 --> 16:17.677
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

16:25.653 --> 16:27.386
- Salud.
- Salud.

16:27.521 --> 16:32.058
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

16:32.192 --> 16:34.927
- That's rum.
- No shit. That a problem?

16:34.929 --> 16:38.731
- No, it just, um,
takes me back.

16:38.733 --> 16:41.333
- Oh. Check it.

16:41.469 --> 16:43.602
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

16:43.604 --> 16:46.204
<i> [foreboding music]</i>

16:46.206 --> 16:47.339
- Looks good.

16:47.341 --> 16:50.409
- Ruth.
- Hmm?

16:50.544 --> 16:52.411
- I'm gonna go
to the restroom.

16:52.413 --> 16:55.181
- Hey, wait a minute.
Let's have a chat.

16:57.418 --> 17:00.286
- For God's sake, Ruth.
Let him breathe.

17:00.421 --> 17:02.421
Sorry, old chap.

17:02.556 --> 17:03.689
- Another rum.

17:03.824 --> 17:06.692
<i> [mysterious music]</i>

17:06.827 --> 17:14.000
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:21.375 --> 17:24.343
[indistinct chatter]

17:27.515 --> 17:30.582
<i> [upbeat music playing]</i>

17:30.584 --> 17:37.757
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:40.528 --> 17:42.728
[guitar playing]

17:42.863 --> 17:50.036
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:52.473 --> 17:54.607
Hey, I'm looking
for the cartographer.

17:54.742 --> 17:56.475
Uh, yeah, thank you.

17:56.477 --> 17:57.743
- It's a good one.

17:57.878 --> 18:04.951
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

18:12.760 --> 18:14.227
- Are you lost?

18:18.032 --> 18:20.366
- You're the cartographer?

18:20.501 --> 18:21.868
- Yeah. Come in.

18:29.710 --> 18:31.910
You're staring.

18:31.912 --> 18:34.780
- Yeah. Sorry.
You remind me of someone.

18:35.916 --> 18:38.317
- Where you trying to go?
- The Tail.

18:39.720 --> 18:41.119
- Why you want to go there?

18:41.121 --> 18:43.121
- Get back to my family.

18:43.123 --> 18:45.724
- Yeah? You're a dad?

18:45.726 --> 18:47.259
- We have a daughter.

18:47.395 --> 18:50.929
- Yeah, well, being a parent
makes you do crazy things.

18:51.065 --> 18:54.266
<i> [soft music]</i>

18:54.402 --> 18:55.467
- Okay.

18:55.469 --> 18:58.470
So getting to the Tail,

18:58.606 --> 19:00.806
that's the easy part.

19:00.941 --> 19:03.542
Getting in the Tail,
you need the word.

19:03.678 --> 19:05.811
- Okay. What's the word?

19:05.946 --> 19:07.946
- I don't know the word, but...

19:07.948 --> 19:10.482
"Most will run,
some will seek.

19:10.484 --> 19:13.151
"Hide or cheat,
we always meet.

19:13.153 --> 19:15.888
I present,
past and future keep."

19:15.890 --> 19:17.023
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

19:17.157 --> 19:18.490
- Is that a riddle?

19:18.626 --> 19:20.092
Oh, I hate riddles.
- Okay, that's enough.

19:20.094 --> 19:21.493
- Give it to me again.
- That's enough.

19:21.629 --> 19:23.696
[speaking Spanish]
- Hey, hey, hey, hey. Okay.

19:23.831 --> 19:25.831
Just let go of my arm.
Man! Hey!

19:25.966 --> 19:27.233
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

19:27.368 --> 19:29.235
Ah! [groans]

19:29.370 --> 19:31.169
<i> - Gracias.</i>
- All yours.

19:31.305 --> 19:33.772
[gun clicks]
- Okay.

19:33.774 --> 19:35.241
- I told you he stunk.

19:35.376 --> 19:37.576
- Easy, okay? I just
had some personal business.

19:37.578 --> 19:39.245
- Oh, you're gonna have
to do better than that, man.

19:39.380 --> 19:40.847
- You botched the pick-up,
you forgot your password,

19:40.981 --> 19:42.514
and I know that you talked
to the Forger

19:42.516 --> 19:43.716
earlier about the Tail.

19:43.718 --> 19:45.183
- I vouched for you, Andre.

19:45.185 --> 19:46.985
You told me you wouldn't ask
any questions.

19:46.987 --> 19:48.721
- I was just covering my back.
- Let's pop him.

19:48.723 --> 19:51.323
We can't risk this shit.
- Get that shit out of my face.

19:51.325 --> 19:52.725
You tell them to stand down.

19:52.727 --> 19:54.326
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

19:54.328 --> 19:56.062
You need me, or you never
would've brought me this far.

19:56.196 --> 19:58.997
- We only need you
for the meeting, Andre.

19:59.133 --> 20:01.467
After that, we're done.
Do you understand?

20:01.602 --> 20:03.535
- Fine by me.
- Put the gun down, Ruth.

20:03.537 --> 20:09.341
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:09.343 --> 20:11.944
What you don't know
might hurt you.

20:12.080 --> 20:17.283
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:21.756 --> 20:24.823
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

20:24.825 --> 20:31.998
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:36.170 --> 20:39.038
<i> [lively music playing</i>
<i> in distance]</i>

20:39.173 --> 20:42.041
<i> [singers singing in Spanish]</i>

20:42.176 --> 20:44.109
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:44.245 --> 20:46.845
- They're okay, Alex.

20:46.981 --> 20:50.049
Just him. Bring him down.

20:50.051 --> 20:57.223
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:59.060 --> 21:01.126
Look at that, he showed up.

21:01.262 --> 21:02.595
- That was the plan, right?
- Shut up.

21:02.730 --> 21:05.197
- Hey, we're gonna
be friends here, maybe.

21:05.332 --> 21:07.400
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

21:07.534 --> 21:09.402
How you doing?
Good to see you.

21:09.536 --> 21:11.136
- You too.
- Hey. You hungry?

21:11.138 --> 21:13.406
You're always hungry.
Hey, let's get you some claws.

21:13.540 --> 21:16.275
Some claws, some legs,
oysters over here.

21:16.411 --> 21:19.812
- Oysters, claws, coming up.

21:19.947 --> 21:21.013
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

21:21.148 --> 21:22.215
- Have a seat.

21:22.349 --> 21:29.522
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

21:40.101 --> 21:41.701
- All right. Uh...

21:43.238 --> 21:45.370
- Sam.
- This is--

21:45.506 --> 21:48.974
Sam, this is Joseph Wilford.

21:48.976 --> 21:50.242
- Joe.
- Joe.

21:50.377 --> 21:52.911
This is the guy
I was telling you about.

21:52.913 --> 21:55.114
- You all right?

21:55.249 --> 21:57.750
- I guess we'll see.

21:58.385 --> 22:00.252
- Here we go.

22:00.387 --> 22:01.787
- Go ahead. Dive in.

22:03.524 --> 22:06.391
- I'm not really here
for the seafood or the company.

22:06.527 --> 22:08.327
The crab's a filthy creature.

22:09.530 --> 22:11.464
- He warned me
I wouldn't like you.

22:12.667 --> 22:14.267
- He said the same about you,
old chap,

22:14.401 --> 22:16.401
but I told him
it doesn't really matter,

22:16.403 --> 22:18.403
'cause I'll forget you, anyway.

22:19.073 --> 22:20.473
- I heard about
that heat uptrain.

22:20.608 --> 22:22.741
Two dead G-men.
That kind of sours the deal.

22:22.877 --> 22:25.010
- Oh, hey, that's on me.

22:25.146 --> 22:27.346
There were no witnesses.

22:27.348 --> 22:30.215
Joe bailed me out.

22:30.217 --> 22:32.084
Got us across the border clean.

22:32.219 --> 22:34.820
<i> [tense music]</i>

22:34.822 --> 22:37.623
- Well, it's not my problem,
as long as I get what I need.

22:37.758 --> 22:43.228
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

22:43.364 --> 22:46.231
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

22:46.367 --> 22:53.472
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:08.789 --> 23:09.989
- Let's have a look. Shall we?

23:10.124 --> 23:13.859
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:13.995 --> 23:15.460
- It's legit.

23:15.596 --> 23:18.130
- Yeah. It's all good.

23:18.265 --> 23:19.865
- Good.

23:20.001 --> 23:22.935
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:23.070 --> 23:25.938
- By the power vested in me,
you assholes are under arrest.

23:26.073 --> 23:27.472
[guns clicking]
- [yelps]

23:27.474 --> 23:30.676
No! No, don't shoot!
[people screaming]

23:30.678 --> 23:31.944
<i> - ♪ Life is getting better</i>
<i> every day, oh, yeah ♪</i>

23:32.079 --> 23:33.612
- Go.

23:33.614 --> 23:36.015
<i> - ♪ Things are looking up</i>
<i> in every way ♪</i>

23:36.150 --> 23:37.750
[gunshots]
[people screaming]

23:37.885 --> 23:39.418
<i> - ♪ My troubles</i>
<i> and my worries ♪</i>

23:39.554 --> 23:41.620
<i> ♪ Were too much</i>
<i> for me to bear ♪</i>

23:41.622 --> 23:43.822
<i> ♪ So finally, in despair ♪</i>

23:43.824 --> 23:45.891
<i> ♪ I threw my troubles</i>
<i> in the air ♪</i>

23:45.893 --> 23:48.093
<i> ♪ And take upon your shoulders</i>
<i> all the woes and cares ♪</i>

23:48.229 --> 23:49.762
- Help me!

23:49.897 --> 23:53.699
<i> - ♪ Of everybody else</i>
<i> instead of yours ♪</i>

23:53.701 --> 23:57.036
<i> ♪ This may seem impossibly</i>
<i> improbable to you ♪</i>

23:57.171 --> 24:02.107
<i> ♪ When suddenly you'll find</i>
<i> that everyone is singing too ♪</i>

24:02.109 --> 24:05.778
<i> ♪ Things are lookin' up</i>
<i> in every way, oh, yeah ♪</i>

24:05.913 --> 24:09.982
<i> ♪ Things are lookin' up</i>
<i> in every way ♪</i>

24:10.117 --> 24:11.784
- [grunting]

24:11.919 --> 24:13.786
<i> - ♪ Things are lookin' up</i>
<i> in every way ♪</i>

24:13.921 --> 24:15.254
- Get up.

24:17.124 --> 24:18.724
Modern dance recital?

24:19.994 --> 24:21.660
That was the kids' troupe.

24:21.662 --> 24:23.396
[chuckles]
Let's go.

24:23.530 --> 24:26.265
<i> [tense music]</i>

24:26.401 --> 24:28.133
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:28.269 --> 24:31.136
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

24:31.272 --> 24:35.408
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:35.542 --> 24:37.009
You're in a world
of trouble now.

24:37.144 --> 24:40.746
- Why am I not surprised
you're like this over here too?

24:40.748 --> 24:43.282
- Firing squad's at midnight.

24:43.418 --> 24:45.684
- Wait. Hey, hey.
Firing squad?

24:45.820 --> 24:46.952
- Take care.

24:46.954 --> 24:53.893
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:02.303 --> 25:05.104
- Do you want forgiveness?

25:05.106 --> 25:06.105
- Pike?

25:06.107 --> 25:11.977
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:12.113 --> 25:13.245
Oh, God.

25:13.380 --> 25:14.847
- Indeed, brother.

25:14.982 --> 25:16.883
Your hour draws nigh.

25:17.919 --> 25:20.519
Confess your sins,
and you will be absolved.

25:20.521 --> 25:21.921
- Of what?

25:22.056 --> 25:24.790
- There are a pile of bodies
in the cantina.

25:24.925 --> 25:27.392
Start there.
- [scoffs]

25:27.394 --> 25:29.528
I just want to go home.

25:29.664 --> 25:30.996
- How can you get back home

25:31.132 --> 25:33.633
if you don't even know
what you're looking for?

25:35.670 --> 25:37.736
- The Tail Boss
can send me home.

25:37.738 --> 25:39.939
- That's where you're
very wrong.

25:41.542 --> 25:43.276
- What do you
really want from me?

25:43.410 --> 25:45.878
You threatened New Eden.

25:46.013 --> 25:48.080
I didn't have any choice, Pike.

25:48.215 --> 25:52.017
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:52.153 --> 25:55.954
- May God have mercy
on your soul.

25:55.956 --> 25:57.622
- No. Pike.

25:57.624 --> 25:59.424
Pike, I won.

25:59.560 --> 26:01.226
I get to keep my secrets, Pike!

26:01.362 --> 26:03.362
That was the deal!

26:03.498 --> 26:04.830
Pike!

26:07.302 --> 26:10.436
[beeping, whirring]

26:17.378 --> 26:20.479
- How's he doing?
- No change.

26:21.716 --> 26:23.248
What is she doing here?

26:23.250 --> 26:25.050
- Oh. I know, Zarah.

26:25.052 --> 26:27.786
But you worked with her
in the Nightcar.

26:27.788 --> 26:29.922
You know what she can do.

26:30.057 --> 26:32.658
- I don't know if it'll work,
but I can try.

26:35.129 --> 26:38.397
- Guess it couldn't hurt.
I could use a break.

26:38.533 --> 26:40.065
- Yeah.

26:40.067 --> 26:43.336
- Josie, want to get
a cup of coffee?

26:43.470 --> 26:44.937
- Yeah, sure.

26:50.678 --> 26:53.212
- Okay. Now what happens?

26:53.214 --> 26:54.279
- I try to reach him.

26:54.281 --> 26:55.581
- Okay. Let's go.

27:08.896 --> 27:10.963
- Andre.

27:11.098 --> 27:13.632
Listen.

27:13.634 --> 27:15.568
Listen to your breath.

27:16.571 --> 27:18.771
Feel the in and out

27:18.906 --> 27:21.073
as the air fills your lungs.

27:22.043 --> 27:24.910
<i> [soft music]</i>

27:25.046 --> 27:31.917
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:32.053 --> 27:33.586
<i> [intense music]</i>

27:33.721 --> 27:39.192
Andre, if you can hear me,
move towards my voice.

27:39.326 --> 27:41.727
Remember your body.

27:41.862 --> 27:44.997
The feel of your daughter
in your arms.

27:45.132 --> 27:47.834
Someone you love
whispering in your ear.

27:49.203 --> 27:50.803
Remember yourself.

27:51.739 --> 27:52.805
[clock ticking]

27:52.940 --> 27:54.873
<i> You're searching for something</i>

27:54.875 --> 27:57.009
<i> but you don't know what.</i>

27:57.144 --> 27:58.811
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:58.946 --> 28:00.879
You're trapped, Andre.

28:00.881 --> 28:04.083
You're holding onto something
that isn't real.

28:04.085 --> 28:05.550
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:05.686 --> 28:08.487
<i> Move towards me.</i>

28:08.623 --> 28:10.355
Come back.

28:10.357 --> 28:12.024
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:12.159 --> 28:15.828
Whatever's keeping you here,
face it.

28:16.030 --> 28:17.530
And come home.

28:24.171 --> 28:27.039
<i> [tense music]</i>

28:27.174 --> 28:29.642
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:29.777 --> 28:32.645
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

28:32.780 --> 28:39.585
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:48.262 --> 28:49.328
- [grunts]

28:49.464 --> 28:56.602
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:57.672 --> 29:00.806
[grunting]

29:01.676 --> 29:05.144
[groaning]

29:05.280 --> 29:08.413
Andre. You made it.

29:08.415 --> 29:10.816
You're a good man.

29:10.951 --> 29:12.885
I caught a bullet
on the way out.

29:15.022 --> 29:17.823
You've got to keep going.

29:17.958 --> 29:19.758
- What do you mean?

29:19.760 --> 29:21.694
- To the Tail.

29:21.829 --> 29:24.163
You're nearly there.

29:24.299 --> 29:28.634
Here. Take it.

29:28.769 --> 29:30.035
- What is it?

29:30.171 --> 29:33.039
- It's our gift
to the Tail Boss.

29:35.376 --> 29:37.543
Good luck.

29:46.321 --> 29:50.556
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:03.837 --> 30:06.838
<i> [soft music]</i>

30:06.840 --> 30:12.778
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:12.914 --> 30:15.781
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

30:15.917 --> 30:23.055
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:39.741 --> 30:41.941
- I recognize this.

30:42.076 --> 30:44.209
You've glommed on
to some theory.

30:44.211 --> 30:47.947
This is step one,
"research frenzy."

30:48.082 --> 30:51.283
Step two would be
"soak in the bathtub"

30:51.419 --> 30:52.484
if you had one.

30:52.486 --> 30:54.353
So what is it?
- Could be nothing.

30:54.488 --> 30:56.756
- Well, it's clearly something
because you called me in here.

30:56.890 --> 30:58.290
- I need charts, Alex.

30:58.426 --> 31:00.159
And my instruments--
parallel ruler, compass.

31:00.294 --> 31:02.962
- So that you can slash
your guard in the throat?

31:03.097 --> 31:04.897
- Is it true Mr. Layton
is at death's door?

31:05.032 --> 31:07.633
- That's need-to-know.
- Fine.

31:07.769 --> 31:09.501
Leave me out of the politics.

31:09.637 --> 31:11.837
But this...

31:11.839 --> 31:13.239
this is big, Alex.

31:13.374 --> 31:16.575
Give everyone some real hope,
especially you.

31:16.710 --> 31:22.047
If you don't help me,
we may never know.

31:22.049 --> 31:26.185
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:28.656 --> 31:31.590
- Old Ivan's Way.

31:31.725 --> 31:33.593
- I'm sorry.

31:33.727 --> 31:36.195
It wasn't supposed
to go to knives.

31:36.330 --> 31:40.332
- God, I hated the Tail.
All of its customs.

31:40.334 --> 31:44.069
Like people playing the piano
like it wasn't a bunk bed.

31:44.205 --> 31:46.138
Meanwhile,
Andre's teaching children

31:46.273 --> 31:50.075
how to breed rats
just so we can eat.

31:50.211 --> 31:54.480
- Oh, we had some dark times.
- Yeah. But you know,

31:54.616 --> 31:57.283
you and Andre took
such good care of everyone.

31:57.418 --> 31:59.018
I mean, the two of you just--

31:59.153 --> 32:01.153
you really bring out
the best in each other.

32:01.155 --> 32:04.556
- I don't know.
- You do.

32:04.692 --> 32:07.959
You know, it used
to really threaten me,

32:07.961 --> 32:10.463
but it doesn't anymore.

32:12.300 --> 32:15.535
Andre and I are better as
co-parents than as a couple.

32:21.709 --> 32:24.310
Josie...

32:24.312 --> 32:26.578
I never should have
turned my back on you.

32:26.714 --> 32:27.847
I--
- Hey.

32:27.982 --> 32:29.915
You were backed against a wall.

32:30.051 --> 32:31.984
I don't blame you.

32:32.119 --> 32:34.720
Never have.

32:34.722 --> 32:36.922
- I'm just so glad
you're here with me today.

32:36.924 --> 32:38.224
I...

32:40.528 --> 32:44.463
And I'm glad
that Andre has you too.

32:54.608 --> 32:55.842
- [sighs]

32:57.945 --> 32:59.879
Hello?

33:00.014 --> 33:01.747
- What do you want?

33:01.749 --> 33:04.350
- Josie.

33:04.352 --> 33:07.619
Sorry...you're the Tail Boss?

33:07.621 --> 33:09.221
- You didn't answer
my question.

33:09.357 --> 33:12.224
- No. Hey.
My name is Andre Layton,

33:12.360 --> 33:15.061
and I'm trying
to get back home.

33:17.098 --> 33:19.231
Do you know me?

33:19.367 --> 33:21.501
- No, but the Tail Boss
knows everyone.

33:22.436 --> 33:23.969
"Most will run,
but some will seek.

33:24.105 --> 33:26.038
"But hide or cheat,
we'll always meet.

33:26.040 --> 33:27.707
I present,
past and future keep."

33:27.841 --> 33:30.710
Who am I?
- Josie.

33:30.844 --> 33:32.512
- Who am I, Mr. Layton?

33:34.648 --> 33:35.882
- Death.

33:43.124 --> 33:44.456
- Been expecting you.

33:44.592 --> 33:46.058
Didn't think
you'd know the word.

33:46.193 --> 33:48.193
- Yeah. I guess.

33:48.329 --> 33:51.330
I know it too well, actually.

33:51.465 --> 33:53.733
I guess I'm trying
to escape it.

33:53.867 --> 33:55.535
- Death isn't the enemy.

33:55.669 --> 33:58.604
You're here 'cause you're
scared of something.

33:58.740 --> 34:01.006
- Oh, yeah?

34:01.142 --> 34:02.874
What am I afraid of?

34:02.876 --> 34:03.943
- I don't know,

34:04.078 --> 34:05.745
but you're gonna
have to face it.

34:05.879 --> 34:07.747
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

34:07.881 --> 34:09.348
He's here.

34:09.483 --> 34:13.286
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:22.896 --> 34:25.431
- You run the train.

34:27.501 --> 34:29.902
- Yes, I do.

34:30.571 --> 34:32.939
- The power's in the Tail.
It's upside-down.

34:34.108 --> 34:36.108
- There's no up, no down.

34:36.243 --> 34:37.777
The train is cyclical.

34:37.911 --> 34:39.111
It's a cruel loop.

34:39.246 --> 34:40.712
- Right.
I saw the map.

34:40.714 --> 34:42.248
A snake eating its tail.

34:42.383 --> 34:44.116
<i> [solemn music]</i>

34:44.251 --> 34:46.118
How do I get back
out of a loop?

34:46.120 --> 34:47.319
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:47.455 --> 34:50.055
- Thank you, Josie.

34:50.191 --> 34:53.793
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:53.928 --> 34:54.794
You like her.

34:54.929 --> 34:57.329
- It's complicated.

34:57.465 --> 34:59.799
- It's never as complicated
as it seems.

34:59.934 --> 35:01.667
You bring me a gift?

35:01.669 --> 35:03.068
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:03.070 --> 35:05.404
I have something for you too.

35:05.539 --> 35:07.406
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:07.541 --> 35:10.742
- That's Zarah's handwriting.
- Read it to me.

35:10.744 --> 35:17.683
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:21.623 --> 35:27.627
- "My little soul,
I haven't seen your face yet

35:27.761 --> 35:30.362
"or held you in my arms,

35:30.364 --> 35:35.034
"but my love for you
is already limitless.

35:35.169 --> 35:39.905
You aren't just my child.
You're the future."

35:39.907 --> 35:41.641
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:41.775 --> 35:43.108
Liana?

35:43.110 --> 35:46.045
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:46.180 --> 35:49.715
- Hi.
- Hi.

35:49.851 --> 35:52.117
[chuckles]

35:52.253 --> 35:54.987
No, this is--
this isn't your future.

35:55.122 --> 35:56.522
It's not.

35:56.524 --> 35:58.257
I'm going back for you.

35:58.392 --> 36:01.327
I--I can get you out of this.
I can break the cycle.

36:01.462 --> 36:03.995
- Look at what you brought me.

36:03.997 --> 36:05.197
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:05.333 --> 36:07.066
- You're not here
to face your death.

36:07.201 --> 36:08.267
- Pike's bomb.

36:08.402 --> 36:09.869
- You're here to face mine.

36:10.004 --> 36:12.204
[beeping]

36:12.206 --> 36:14.606
[rapid beeping]

36:14.608 --> 36:15.274
- Liana!

36:15.409 --> 36:18.477
<i> [echoing] Liana!</i>

36:18.612 --> 36:25.585
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:27.021 --> 36:29.154
[high-pitched ringing]

36:29.290 --> 36:32.124
- Andre. Andre, wake up.

36:35.096 --> 36:37.296
That was a rough one, huh?

36:37.431 --> 36:41.967
- Asha? What am I doing here?

36:42.103 --> 36:44.036
Liana was supposed
to send me home.

36:44.171 --> 36:46.038
- This is your home.

36:46.173 --> 36:49.041
<i> [disquieting music]</i>

36:49.176 --> 36:53.445
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:53.581 --> 36:56.248
- No. I'm supposed to be
on Snowpiercer.

36:56.250 --> 36:58.518
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:58.652 --> 37:00.920
- This hell
is the only home you know.

37:01.055 --> 37:08.227
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:10.331 --> 37:12.464
- I'm close to the answer.

37:12.600 --> 37:14.467
- Don't look in there.

37:17.872 --> 37:20.205
[clanking]

37:20.341 --> 37:21.908
Lunch is ready.

37:27.882 --> 37:30.082
- Tomato soup
and a grilled cheese.

37:30.217 --> 37:31.717
- Hmm?

37:33.288 --> 37:35.688
- A memory.

37:35.823 --> 37:37.623
- Look, we shouldn't dwell
on the past.

37:37.758 --> 37:39.091
We've got enough
to worry about

37:39.226 --> 37:41.427
just trying to stay alive.

37:43.498 --> 37:45.030
- What's in there?

37:45.032 --> 37:48.033
<i> [tense music]</i>

37:48.035 --> 37:49.368
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:49.370 --> 37:50.503
What are you keeping from me?

37:50.638 --> 37:53.973
- Andre.
- Show me. Give me the key.

37:53.975 --> 37:56.509
- No. No! Get off!

37:56.644 --> 37:59.778
- Asha.
- [grunts]

37:59.914 --> 38:01.514
Stop! Stop it!

38:01.648 --> 38:05.584
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:05.586 --> 38:08.854
You're not gonna like
what you find in there, okay?

38:08.990 --> 38:12.124
[distant booming]

38:12.259 --> 38:14.860
[distant crashing]

38:14.996 --> 38:17.196
Shh.

38:17.198 --> 38:18.731
[whispers] Marauders.

38:18.866 --> 38:24.136
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:24.271 --> 38:25.604
- [whispers] Marauders?

38:25.606 --> 38:27.139
The guys that killed everyone?

38:27.274 --> 38:29.542
- Not all, but most.
- Shit.

38:37.618 --> 38:41.354
[breathing heavily]

38:41.488 --> 38:48.661
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:04.179 --> 39:07.413
[wind whistling]

39:10.117 --> 39:12.184
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

39:12.319 --> 39:15.187
[gunshots]
[gun clicking]

39:15.322 --> 39:22.395
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:41.348 --> 39:42.214
[gunshot]

39:42.349 --> 39:49.422
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:59.900 --> 40:01.300
- Asha!

40:01.302 --> 40:08.307
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:08.309 --> 40:09.842
Asha!

40:09.977 --> 40:11.310
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:11.446 --> 40:14.447
[grunting]

40:14.582 --> 40:21.754
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:34.601 --> 40:36.535
- [screaming]

40:36.671 --> 40:40.273
[grunting]

40:40.407 --> 40:47.580
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:48.549 --> 40:51.651
[grunting]

40:54.021 --> 40:57.022
- This is where it started,

40:57.024 --> 40:59.224
where I first saw New Eden.

40:59.226 --> 41:00.959
[breathing heavily]

41:00.961 --> 41:03.029
- You don't need
to look in there.

41:05.432 --> 41:07.700
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

41:07.835 --> 41:10.503
- You told me
not to let you see it.

41:10.637 --> 41:15.908
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:16.043 --> 41:18.778
- I made it up.

41:20.315 --> 41:22.715
- Andre. Dr. Pelton!

41:22.850 --> 41:26.586
It's okay, it's okay.
You're back.

41:35.563 --> 41:36.929
- Hey.

41:39.033 --> 41:41.967
I--I thought you'd want to know

41:41.969 --> 41:44.504
Dr. Pelton thinks
he's gonna be okay.

41:44.638 --> 41:48.974
No lasting brain damage
or anything.

41:48.976 --> 41:52.177
So...

41:52.179 --> 41:56.949
thank you for helping him.

41:58.319 --> 42:00.319
- You're a really good friend
to Andre.

42:00.454 --> 42:05.190
Bess, you care so much
for other people,

42:05.326 --> 42:07.059
but you won't let
anyone care for you.

42:07.194 --> 42:08.594
Why is that?

42:08.730 --> 42:11.263
<i> [soft music]</i>

42:11.399 --> 42:14.133
- It's been a long day, Audrey.

42:14.268 --> 42:21.340
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

42:31.219 --> 42:33.953
[door beeping]

42:34.088 --> 42:35.687
- Oh, thanks.

42:35.689 --> 42:37.489
- Hey.
- Hey.

42:37.625 --> 42:40.893
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

42:41.028 --> 42:42.562
Oh...

42:42.696 --> 42:44.363
You had us scared.

42:48.770 --> 42:50.436
Are you all right?

42:52.706 --> 42:54.774
- What if...

42:54.908 --> 43:01.180
I was so desperate
to give everyone a future...

43:01.315 --> 43:04.617
that I made one up?

43:06.387 --> 43:10.656
I can't lead this train
if all I have is a lie.

43:10.658 --> 43:12.658
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

43:12.660 --> 43:14.059
[exhales shakily]

43:14.061 --> 43:20.866
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

43:20.868 --> 43:23.535
- After the Atacama,
what route did you take?

43:23.537 --> 43:25.937
- I'm not telling you that.

43:25.939 --> 43:27.607
What is all this?

43:27.741 --> 43:30.542
- Come with me.

43:30.678 --> 43:34.146
After our trains separated,
I followed your trail,

43:34.148 --> 43:36.682
trying to guess intentions,

43:36.684 --> 43:39.885
near-term destination
versus long-term trajectory.

43:39.887 --> 43:43.155
I couldn't catch you.
I had to intercept.

43:43.290 --> 43:45.424
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

43:45.559 --> 43:47.026
See?

43:47.161 --> 43:49.028
- Whoa, okay.

43:49.163 --> 43:52.632
- So about three months in,
I thought I caught a break--

43:52.766 --> 43:55.767
a track switch signal
near Marseille.

43:55.903 --> 43:58.504
We followed it there
but found no sign of you.

43:58.506 --> 44:00.105
- Well, yeah, 'cause
that was the wrong continent.

44:00.241 --> 44:01.707
We were nowhere near France.

44:01.843 --> 44:04.576
- So the question is,
if it wasn't you, who was it?

44:04.712 --> 44:06.778
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

44:06.780 --> 44:08.047
- A signal error.

44:08.182 --> 44:11.651
- No. I don't think
it was a malfunction, Alex.

44:11.785 --> 44:14.520
I believe it was your mother.

44:14.522 --> 44:18.724
That Melanie is alive.

44:18.726 --> 44:20.125
[chuckles]

44:20.261 --> 44:22.395
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

44:25.066 --> 44:28.133
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

44:28.135 --> 44:35.308
<i> ♪ ♪</i>
